        public MenuFrame​(java.io.PrintWriter socketOut,
                 java.net.Socket aSocket,
                 java.io.BufferedReader stdIn,
                 java.io.BufferedReader socketIn,
                 java.io.ObjectInputStream objectIn,
                 Student student)
        Constructor for class MenuFrame, which initializes server communication variables from the GUI (and calls the super constructor to finalize the MenuFrame, with the exception of "student")
        Parameters:
        socketOut - is the printWriter to be used as a socketOut
        aSocket - is the Socket to be used as aSocket
        stdIn - is the BufferedReader to be used as stdIn
        socketIn - is the BufferedReader to be used as a socketIn
        objectIn - is the objectInputStream used to read in objects to the frame
        student - is the student to which menu methods are being executed for (eg, a "register for course" call under a specific student

      • displayFrame

        public void displayFrame()
        displayFrame() is the method that creates and displays the menu frame for the user, who can then dictate what actions to take via numerous buttons. The action of these buttons are controlled by a MenuFrameController, which is instantiated at the end of the method
